quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  75,1,I SWEAR by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,and by the self-reproaching soul
  75,3,Does man think We shall never put his bones together again
  75,4,"Indeed, We can remould his very fingers"
  75,5,Yet man would ever deny what is to come
  75,6,"‘When will this be,‘ he asks, ‘this Day of Resurrection?‘"
  75,7,But when the sight of mortals is confounded
  75,8,and the moon eclipsed
  75,9,when sun and moon are joined together
  75,10,"on that day man will ask: ‘Whither shall I flee?‘"
  75,11,"No, there shall be no refuge"
  75,12,"for to your Lord, on that day, all shall be restored"
  75,13,"Indeed, man shall on that day be told of all he did, from first to last"
  75,14,"Indeed, man shall bear witness against himself"
  75,15,plead as he may with his excuses
  75,16,You¹ need not move your tongue too fast to learn this revelation
  75,17,We Ourself shall see to its collection and recital
  75,18,"When We read it, follow its words attentively"
  75,19,We shall Ourself explain its meaning
  75,20,No! But you² love this fleeting life
  75,21,and ignore the life to come
  75,22,On that day there shall be joyous faces
  75,23,looking towards their Lord
  75,24,On that day there shall be mournful faces
  75,25,dreading some great affliction
  75,26,No! But when a man‘s soul is about to leave him
  75,27,"and those around him say: ‘Will no one save him?‘"
  75,28,When he knows it is the final parting
  75,29,and leg and leg are twined ―
  75,30,on that day to your Lord he shall be driven
  75,31,For in this life he neither believed nor prayed
  75,32,"he denied the Truth and, turning his back"
  75,33,went to his kin elated with pride
  75,34,Well have you deserved this doom; well have you deserved it
  75,35,"Well have you deserved this doom: too well have you deserved it"
  75,36,"Does man think he will be left alone, to no purpose"
  75,37,Was he not a drop of ejaculated semen
  75,38,He became a clot of blood;³ then God formed and moulded him
  75,39,and gave him male and female parts
  75,40,"Has He no power, then, to raise the dead to life"